**Goal**: Verify ticket work quality

**Path**:
1. Check folder structure against `rule.ticket.coding-and-folder-structure.v1`
2. Check `plan.md` against `rule.ticket.plan.v1`
3. Check `progress.md` against `rule.ticket.progress.v1`
4. Review validation evidence against `rule.ticket.validation.v1`
5. Verify commit discipline per `rule.ticket.workflow.v1`

**Time**: 15-30 minutes per ticket

## Common Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Starting a New Ticket
1. User provides ticket ID and description
2. Execute `rule.ticket.coding-and-folder-structure.v1` -> creates folder structure
3. Execute `rule.ticket.plan.v1` -> creates plan.md
4. Execute `rule.ticket.complexity-assessment.v1` -> determines track
5. Execute `rule.ticket.context.v1` -> initializes context.md
6. Execute `rule.ticket.progress.v1` -> first entry
7. Update `tickets/current.md` with ticket ID

### Scenario 2: Switching Tickets
1. Execute `rule.ticket.switching-discipline.v1`
2. Pause current ticket (update context.md with PAUSED)
3. Log switch in progress.md of both tickets
4. Update `tickets/current.md`
5. Resume target ticket (read context.md for state)

### Scenario 3: Completing a Ticket
1. Execute `rule.ticket.validation.v1` (comprehensive checks)
2. Execute `rule.ticket.recap.v1` -> creates recap.md
3. Execute `rule.ticket.rca.v1` if defect -> creates rca.md
4. Execute `rule.ticket.workflow.v1` closure commit
5. Update `tickets/current.md` (clear active ticket)

### Scenario 4: Claiming Work is Complete
1. Execute `rule.ticket.completion-discipline.v1` self-check
2. Execute `rule.ticket.validation.v1` all 4 levels
3. Document validation evidence in progress.md
4. Only then update context.md to mark complete
5. Proceed to Scenario 3 (completing ticket)

